title: Store Fornestinden
text:
Store Fornestinden is a <a href="mountain">mountain</a> in <a href="Troms%C3%B8%20Municipality">Tromsø Municipality</a> in <a href="Troms%20og%20Finnmark">Troms og Finnmark</a> county, <a href="Norway">Norway</a>. The highest peak of any mountain in the eastern part of the municipality. The tall mountain lies about east of the <a href="Troms%C3%B8%20%28city%29">city of Tromsø</a> and about west of the village of <a href="Lyngseidet">Lyngseidet</a> in the neighboring <a href="Lyngen%20Municipality">Lyngen Municipality</a>. The mountain is on the southern shore of the <a href="Kjosen%20%28Troms%29">Kjosen</a> fjord, an arm of the large <a href="Ullsfjorden">Ullsfjorden</a>.
The mountain consists of two peaks, the highest being Store Fornestinden at . The second peak named Litle Fornestinden, is slightly more northerly with a height of . The mountain is located in the <a href="Lyngen%20Alps">Lyngen Alps</a>, part of the <a href="Scandinavian%20Mountains">Scandinavian Mountains</a>.
